The paper focuses on computer vision and deep learning techniques applied to highway perception scenarios, which suggests that it would likely fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for deep learning to bring about a solution to autonomous driving, which aligns with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The empirical evaluations and use of neural networks also suggest that the paper could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on autonomous driving and real-time systems suggests that the paper could also fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the need for large data sets and the potential for practical applications, which could suggest that it falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
